Working with raster to stars in R

Wyclife Agumba Oluoch (wyclifeoluoch@gmail.com)

2021-12-18 12:27:53

Create raster

  1. This is one of the most interesting bits of the rmarkdown. Kind of Literate Programming.
r <- raster(ncols = 20, nrows = 20)

Fill raster

r[] <- round(rnorm(n = ncell(r)), 2)

Plot raster

plot(r)

Convert raster to stars

s <- st_as_stars(r)

Plot stars

plot(s)

Show pixel values

plot(s, text_values = TRUE, 
     col = terrain.colors(10, alpha = 1), 
     breaks = "equal")
